Introduction¶

This data set contains information about 10,000 movies collected from The Movie Database (TMDb), including user ratings and revenue.

The final two columns ending with _adj show the budget and revenue of the associated movie in terms of 2010 dollars, accounting for inflation over time.

Importing libraries to query data and visual display

In [2]:
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns 
% matplotlib inline

Conclusions¶

In conclusion I would like to say that you can find different result everytime you use a new or multiple filters but for questions I try to answer here shows Action genre dominated last 10 years in movie industry from 20015 to 2005. Public interest in movies genres change over year but Action movies seems to be hit in 60s and 70s and then become very popular in new millineum in pic 1 above.

Drama tends to be overall most common genre and 'Passion of Christ' movie earned most in that category. Rightly skewed Histogram shows this trend in pic 2 above.
